00:15:37,104 --> 00:15:39,189
but when I took over
this department...

237
00:15:39,273 --> 00:15:41,859
it had the worst programming record
in television history.

238
00:15:41,942 --> 00:15:44,736
This network hasn't one show
in the top 20.

239
00:15:44,778 --> 00:15:46,864
This network is an industry joke.

240
00:15:46,947 --> 00:15:50,242
We better start putting together
one winner for next September.

241
00:15:50,284 --> 00:15:52,244
I want a show developed...

242
00:15:52,286 --> 00:15:55,914
based on the activities
of a terrorist group.

243
00:15:55,956 --> 00:15:58,375
"Joseph Stalin and His Merry Band
of Bolsheviks."

244
00:15:58,458 --> 00:16:01,795
I want ideas from you.
That is what you're paid for.

245
00:16:01,879 --> 00:16:05,632
By the way, the next time I send
an audience research report around...

246
00:16:05,716 --> 00:16:08,135
you'd better read it,
or I'll sack the lot of you.

247
00:16:08,218 --> 00:16:09,845
Is that clear?

248
00:16:09,928 --> 00:16:15,601
I'll be on the coast in four weeks. Can
you set up a meeting with Laureen Hobbs?

249
00:16:15,642 --> 00:16:19,271
The business of management
is management.

250
00:16:19,313 --> 00:16:22,691
At the time CCA took control,
the UBS TV network was foundering...

251
00:16:22,774 --> 00:16:26,278
with less than seven percent
of national television revenues...

252
00:16:26,361 --> 00:16:29,239
most network programs being sold
at station rates.

253
00:16:29,323 --> 00:16:32,910
I am pleased to announce I am submitting
to the board of directors a plan...

254
00:16:32,993 --> 00:16:35,704
for the coordination
of the main profit centers...

255
00:16:35,787 --> 00:16:38,749
and with the specific intention
of making each division...

256
00:16:38,832 --> 00:16:41,627
more responsive to management.

257
00:16:41,668 --> 00:16:43,128
Point one.

258
00:16:44,505 --> 00:16:48,008
"The division producing the lowest rate
of return has been the News Division...

259
00:16:48,091 --> 00:16:53,639
with its $98 million budget and its
average annual deficit of $32 million."

260
00:16:54,848 --> 00:16:58,143
I know, historically, news divisions
are expected to lose money.

261
00:16:58,227 --> 00:17:01,063
To our minds, this philosophy
is a wanton fiscal affront...

262
00:17:01,146 --> 00:17:04,816
to be resolutely resisted.

263
00:17:04,900 --> 00:17:10,364
The new plan calls for local news to be
transferred to Owned Stations Divisions.

264
00:17:10,447 --> 00:17:13,951
News Radio would be transferred to
the UBS Radio Division...

265
00:17:14,034 --> 00:17:18,121
and the News Division would be reduced
from an independent division...

266
00:17:18,205 --> 00:17:22,709
to a department accountable
to network.

267
00:17:27,631 --> 00:17:31,093
- What was that all about, Ed?
- This is not the time.

268
00:17:31,176 --> 00:17:33,095
Why wasn't I told about this?

269
00:17:33,178 --> 00:17:37,474
Why was I led up onto that podium and
humiliated in front of the stockholders?

270
00:17:37,558 --> 00:17:39,977
Goddamn it! I spoke to John Wheeler
this morning...

271
00:17:40,060 --> 00:17:42,688
and he assured me
that the News Division was safe.

272
00:17:42,729 --> 00:17:44,982
If you want me to resign,
that's a bad way to do it.

273
00:17:45,065 --> 00:17:47,943
We'll talk about this tomorrow
at our regular morning meeting.

274
00:18:00,080 --> 00:18:02,040
Roll VTA.

275
00:18:02,082 --> 00:18:04,334
Bring it up on one.
Ready now.

276
00:18:05,210 --> 00:18:09,173
In five, four, three, two...

277
00:18:09,256 --> 00:18:11,425
- One.
- One TVA.

278
00:18:12,885 --> 00:18:14,303
And...

279
00:18:16,138 --> 00:18:17,556
cue announcer.

280
00:18:17,639 --> 00:18:19,600
The "UBS Evening News"...

281
00:18:20,809 --> 00:18:22,853
with Howard Beale.

282
00:18:22,936 --> 00:18:24,813
Ready two.

283
00:18:24,897 --> 00:18:26,398
Two. Cue power.

284
00:18:26,481 --> 00:18:30,527
Good evening.
Today is Wednesday, September 24...

285
00:18:30,611 --> 00:18:32,529
and this is my last broadcast.

286
00:18:33,947 --> 00:18:35,908
Yesterday I announced
on this program...

287
00:18:35,949 --> 00:18:38,952
that I was going to commit
public suicide...

288
00:18:38,994 --> 00:18:41,538
admittedly an act of madness.

289
00:18:41,622 --> 00:18:44,750
I'll tell you what happened.
I just ran out of bullshit.

290
00:18:44,791 --> 00:18:47,085
- Cut him off.
- Leave him on.

291
00:18:48,545 --> 00:18:49,963
Am I still on?

292
00:18:50,047 --> 00:18:53,133
If this is how he wants to go out,
this is how he goes out.

293
00:18:53,217 --> 00:18:55,469
I just ran out of bullshit.

294
00:18:55,552 --> 00:18:58,013
Mr. Schumacher's here.
Do you want to talk to him?

295
00:18:58,096 --> 00:19:00,015
Bullshit is all the reasons
we give for living.

296
00:19:00,098 --> 00:19:04,394
If we can't think up reasons of our own,
we always have the God bullshit.

297
00:19:04,478 --> 00:19:06,313
- We don't know why we go through...
- What is it?

298
00:19:06,396 --> 00:19:08,857
Pointless pain,
humiliation and decay.

299
00:19:08,941 --> 00:19:12,861
There better be someone, somewhere
who does know. That's the God bullshit.

300
00:19:12,945 --> 00:19:16,365
He's saying that life is bullshit.
It is. What are you screaming about?

301
00:19:16,448 --> 00:19:19,868
Man is a noble creature who can order
his own world. Who needs God?

302
00:19:21,078 --> 00:19:24,957
If there's anybody who can look around
this demented world we live in...

303
00:19:24,998 --> 00:19:28,043
and tell me man
is a noble creature...

304
00:19:28,126 --> 00:19:30,420
believe me,
that man is full of bullshit.

305
00:19:31,505 --> 00:19:35,133
- What's so goddamn funny?
- I can't help it. It's funny.

306
00:19:36,885 --> 00:19:39,847
This is going out live
to 67 affiliates.

307
00:19:39,930 --> 00:19:41,348
Leave him on.

308
00:19:41,431 --> 00:19:45,936
And I was married for 33 years
of shrill, shrieking fraud.

309
00:19:46,019 --> 00:19:49,606
- Mr. Hackett's trying to reach you.
- Tell Mr. Hackett to go fuck himself.

310
00:19:49,690 --> 00:19:52,651
So I don't have any bullshit left.

311
00:19:53,819 --> 00:19:56,780
I just ran out of it, you see.

312
00:20:02,536 --> 00:20:04,997
Mr. Ruddy, could we have
one statement, please?

313
00:20:05,038 --> 00:20:07,166
Sorry, I don't have
all the information yet.

314
00:20:10,627 --> 00:20:14,548
If we could just have one statement
about Mr. Beale.

315
00:20:24,558 --> 00:20:26,018
Max?

316
00:20:34,818 --> 00:20:36,737
I'll want to see Mr. Beale
after this.

317
00:20:39,281 --> 00:20:41,867
The way I hear it,
you were primarily responsible...

318
00:20:41,950 --> 00:20:44,286
for this colossally
stupid prank.

319
00:20:45,037 --> 00:20:47,331
- Is that the fact?
- That's the fact.

320
00:20:47,414 --> 00:20:49,958
It was unconscionable.

321
00:20:53,337 --> 00:20:56,757
- There is nothing more to say.
- I have something to say.

322
00:20:57,925 --> 00:21:00,761
I want to know why that debasement
of the News Division...

323
00:21:00,844 --> 00:21:04,473
announced at the meeting this afternoon
was kept secret from me?

324
00:21:05,724 --> 00:21:08,060
You and I go back 20 years.

325
00:21:08,101 --> 00:21:10,646
I took this job
with your personal assurance...

326
00:21:10,729 --> 00:21:14,483
that you'd back my autonomy
against any encroachment.

327
00:21:14,566 --> 00:21:19,279
But ever since CCA acquired control
of UBS Systems ten months ago...

328
00:21:19,363 --> 00:21:21,698
Hackett's been taking over everything.

329
00:21:21,782 --> 00:21:25,953
Who is running this network?
You or some conglomerate called CCA?

330
00:21:26,036 --> 00:21:28,831
You're president
of the Systems Group.

331
00:21:28,914 --> 00:21:32,459
Hackett's nothing
but a hatchet man for CCA.

332
00:21:32,543 --> 00:21:35,212
Nelson here,
president of the network...

333
00:21:35,295 --> 00:21:38,048
and he hasn't a damned thing to say
about anything anymore.

334
00:21:38,131 --> 00:21:40,717
I told you
at the stockholders' meeting...

335
00:21:40,801 --> 00:21:44,596
that we would discuss all that
at our regular meeting tomorrow morning.

336
00:21:44,680 --> 00:21:47,015
If you had been patient,
I would have explained...

337
00:21:47,099 --> 00:21:49,643
that I, too, thought
Frank Hackett precipitate...

338
00:21:49,726 --> 00:21:52,604
and that the reorganization of the
News Division would not be executed...

339
00:21:52,688 --> 00:21:55,232
until everyone,
specifically you, Max...

340
00:21:55,315 --> 00:21:58,235
had been consulted and satisfied.

341
00:21:59,194 --> 00:22:01,113
Instead, you sulked off
like a child...

342
00:22:01,196 --> 00:22:04,241
and engaged this network
in a shocking and disgraceful episode.

343
00:22:04,324 --> 00:22:06,285
Your position
is no longer tenable...

344
00:22:06,368 --> 00:22:08,704
regardless of how management
is restructured.

345
00:22:10,789 --> 00:22:13,000
I will expect your resignation
at 10:00 tomorrow morning.

346
00:22:13,083 --> 00:22:16,795
We will coordinate our statements
to the least detriment of everyone.

347
00:22:18,964 --> 00:22:22,426
Bob McDonough will take over the News
Division until we sort all this out.

348
00:22:24,511 --> 00:22:27,306
I'd like to see Mr. Beale now.

349
00:22:27,347 --> 00:22:30,142
They're looking for him.
They don't know where he is.

350
00:22:31,476 --> 00:22:35,147
Well, every day, five days a week
for 15 years...

351
00:22:35,230 --> 00:22:38,775
I've been sitting behind that desk,
the dispassionate pundit...

352
00:22:38,859 --> 00:22:41,862
reporting with seemly detachment...

353
00:22:41,945 --> 00:22:45,532
the daily parade of lunacies
that constitute the news.

354
00:22:45,616 --> 00:22:47,034
Just once...

355
00:22:47,117 --> 00:22:49,119
I wanted to say
what I really felt.

356
00:22:49,203 --> 00:22:50,829
Knock it off.

357
00:22:50,871 --> 00:22:52,748
It was, after all, my last one.

358
00:23:09,806 --> 00:23:12,476
- Have the overnight ratings come in?
- They're on your desk.

359
00:23:12,559 --> 00:23:14,478
Have you got
yesterday's overnights?

360
00:23:14,561 --> 00:23:16,772
- Shall I bring them in?
- Yeah.

361
00:23:22,486 --> 00:23:25,572
These are the outlines submitted
by Universal for an hour series.

362
00:23:25,656 --> 00:23:28,700
You needn't bother to read them.
I'll tell them to you.

363
00:23:28,784 --> 00:23:33,372
The first one is set in an eastern
law school, presumably Harvard.

364
00:23:33,455 --> 00:23:36,583
The series is irresistibly entitled
"The New Lawyers."

365
00:23:36,667 --> 00:23:40,045
The running characters are: A crusty
but benign ex-Supreme Court justice...

366
00:23:40,087 --> 00:23:43,549
presumably Oliver Wendell Holmes
by way of Dr. Zorba...

367
00:23:43,590 --> 00:23:47,052
a beautiful girl graduate student,
and the local district attorney...

368
00:23:47,094 --> 00:23:49,054
who is brilliant
and sometimes cuts corners.

369
00:23:49,096 --> 00:23:51,014
Next one.

370
00:23:51,098 --> 00:23:53,058
The second one's called
"The Amazon Squad."

371
00:23:53,141 --> 00:23:54,685
Lady cops.

372
00:23:54,768 --> 00:23:57,604
Running characters include a crusty
but benign police lieutenant...

373
00:23:57,688 --> 00:23:59,982
who's always getting heat
from the commissioner...

374
00:24:00,065 --> 00:24:03,777
a tough, hard-drinking detective who
thinks women belong in the kitchen...

375
00:24:03,861 --> 00:24:07,573
and a brilliant, beautiful young cop
who's fighting the feminist battle.

376
00:24:07,614 --> 00:24:09,700
We're up to our ears in lady cops.

377
00:24:09,783 --> 00:24:12,870
Next is another one of those
investigative reporter shows.

378
00:24:12,953 --> 00:24:15,581
A crusty but benign managing editor
who's always getting...

379
00:24:15,622 --> 00:24:17,749
You know, Barbara...

380
00:24:17,791 --> 00:24:22,087
the Arabs have decided to jack up
the price of oil another 20 percent.

381
00:24:23,088 --> 00:24:26,884
The CIA has been caught opening
Senator Humphrey's mail.

382
00:24:26,967 --> 00:24:30,888
There's a civil war in Angola.
Another one in Beirut.

383
00:24:32,181 --> 00:24:34,725
New York City's still facing default.

384
00:24:34,808 --> 00:24:37,644
They finally caught up
with Patricia Hearst.

385
00:24:37,728 --> 00:24:41,440
And the whole front page
of the Daily News is Howard Beale.

386
00:24:42,566 --> 00:24:46,528
There's also a two-column story
on page one of the Times.

387
00:24:49,323 --> 00:24:51,658
Helen?
Call Mr. Hackett's office.

388
00:24:51,742 --> 00:24:54,161
See if he can give me
a few minutes this morning.

389
00:25:00,792 --> 00:25:05,130
KTNS Kansas City refuses to carry
our "Network News Show" anymore...

390
00:25:05,214 --> 00:25:07,174
unless Beale is taken off the air.

391
00:25:07,216 --> 00:25:09,343
Did you see the overnights
on the "Network News"?

392
00:25:09,426 --> 00:25:12,137
It has an 8 in New York,
a 9 in L. A...

393
00:25:12,221 --> 00:25:14,640
and a 27 share in both cities.

394
00:25:14,723 --> 00:25:17,935
Last night, Howard Beale went on the air
and yelled "bullshit" for two minutes.

395
00:25:18,018 --> 00:25:22,231
I can tell you tonight's show
will get a 30 share at least.

396
00:25:22,314 --> 00:25:25,526
- I think we've lucked into something.
- For God sakes, Diana!

397
00:25:25,609 --> 00:25:28,820
Are you suggesting we put that lunatic
back on the air yelling "bullshit"?

398
00:25:28,862 --> 00:25:32,366
Yes, I think we should put Beale back
on the air tonight and keep him on.

399
00:25:32,449 --> 00:25:35,244
Did you see the news this morning?
Did you see the Times?

400
00:25:35,327 --> 00:25:37,955
We got press coverage on this
you couldn't buy for a million dollars.

401
00:25:38,038 --> 00:25:43,961
That show jumped 5 points in one night.
Tonight's show will be at least 15.

402
00:25:44,044 --> 00:25:48,590
We've just increased our audience by
20 or 30 million people in one night!

403
00:25:48,674 --> 00:25:51,426
You won't get something like this dumped
into your lap the rest of your days.

404
00:25:51,510 --> 00:25:55,639
You can't piss it away. Howard said
last night what every American feels.

405
00:25:55,722 --> 00:26:00,769
He's tired of all the bullshit!
He's articulating the popular rage!

406
00:26:00,853 --> 00:26:02,855
I want that show, Frank.

407
00:26:02,938 --> 00:26:05,148
I can turn that show
into the biggest smash on TV.

408
00:26:05,232 --> 00:26:08,193
It's a news show.
It's not your department.

409
00:26:08,277 --> 00:26:11,029
I see Howard Beale
as a latter-day prophet...

410
00:26:11,071 --> 00:26:15,200
a messianic figure inveighing
against the hypocrisies of our times!

411
00:26:15,242 --> 00:26:17,828
A strip Savonarola
Monday through Friday...

412
00:26:17,911 --> 00:26:20,247
that will just go through the roof!

413
00:26:20,330 --> 00:26:24,293
And I'm talking about
a six-dollar cost per thousand show.

414
00:26:24,376 --> 00:26:27,421
I'm talking about
130,000 dollar minutes.

415
00:26:27,504 --> 00:26:31,258
Figure out the revenues of a strip show
that sells for $100,000 a minute!

416
00:26:31,341 --> 00:26:35,095
One show like that could pull
this network out of the hole!

417
00:26:35,179 --> 00:26:38,390
It's being handed to us on a plate.
Let's not blow it.

418
00:26:39,766 --> 00:26:41,685
Yes.

419
00:26:41,768 --> 00:26:43,937
Tell him I'll be a few minutes.

420
00:26:46,523 --> 00:26:49,735
- Let me think it over.
- Let's not go to committee on this.

421
00:26:49,776 --> 00:26:53,614
It's 10:20. We want Beale in the studio
by 6:30. We don't want to lose momentum.

422
00:26:53,697 --> 00:26:57,784
For God sakes, we're talking about
putting an irresponsible man...

423
00:26:57,868 --> 00:27:00,370
on national television.

424
00:27:10,130 --> 00:27:12,883
I'd like to talk to Legal Affairs,
Herb Thackery...

425
00:27:12,966 --> 00:27:15,552
and Joe Donnelly
in Standards and Practices.

426
00:27:17,221 --> 00:27:20,432
You know I'll be eyeball to eyeball
with Mr. Ruddy on this.

427
00:27:20,474 --> 00:27:23,685
If I'm going to the mat with Ruddy,
I want to be sure of my ground.

428
00:27:23,769 --> 00:27:25,979
My ass is going on the line.

429
00:27:29,399 --> 00:27:31,318
I'll get back to you.

430
00:27:35,072 --> 00:27:37,074
I don't believe the top brass...

431
00:27:37,157 --> 00:27:41,203
of a national television network
is sitting around their Caesar salads...

432
00:27:41,286 --> 00:27:43,622
Top brass of a bankrupt
national television network...

433
00:27:43,664 --> 00:27:46,333
with projected losses
of $150 million.

434
00:27:46,416 --> 00:27:47,835
I don't care!

435
00:27:49,294 --> 00:27:53,215
You can't be seriously proposing,
and the rest of us considering...

436
00:27:53,298 --> 00:27:55,801
putting on a pornographic
network news show.

437
00:27:55,884 --> 00:27:58,136
- The FCC would kill us.
- Sit down, Nelson.

438
00:27:58,178 --> 00:28:01,139
The FCC can't do anything
except rap our knuckles.

439
00:28:01,223 --> 00:28:04,393
I don't even want to think about
the litigious possibilities.

440
00:28:04,476 --> 00:28:07,771
- We could be up to our ears in lawsuits.
- The affiliates won't carry it.

441
00:28:07,855 --> 00:28:10,858
The affiliates will kiss your ass
if you can hand them a hit show.

442
00:28:10,941 --> 00:28:13,193
- But popular reaction...
- We don't know the popular reaction.

443
00:28:13,277 --> 00:28:16,488
- That's what we have to find out.
- The New York Times...

444
00:28:16,530 --> 00:28:19,992
The New York Times doesn't advertise
on our network.

445
00:28:21,910 --> 00:28:26,248
All I know is, this violates
every canon of respectable broadcasting.

446
00:28:26,331 --> 00:28:29,543
We're not a respectable network.
We're a whorehouse network.

447
00:28:29,626 --> 00:28:31,795
We have to take whatever we can get.

448
00:28:33,213 --> 00:28:35,174
I don't want any part of it.

449
00:28:35,257 --> 00:28:37,718
I don't fancy myself
the president of a whorehouse.

450
00:28:37,801 --> 00:28:40,596
That's commendable of you, Nelson.
Now sit down.

451
00:28:41,722 --> 00:28:43,682
Your indignation
has been duly recorded.

452
00:28:43,724 --> 00:28:45,684
You can always resign tomorrow.

453
00:28:47,936 --> 00:28:51,857
What in substance are we proposing?

454
00:28:51,899 --> 00:28:55,861
Merely to add editorial comment
to our network news show.

455
00:28:55,944 --> 00:28:59,698
Brinkley, Sevareid, Reasoner
all have their comments.

456
00:28:59,781 --> 00:29:01,867
Now Howard Beale will have his.

457
00:29:01,950 --> 00:29:05,996
I think we ought to give it a shot,
see what happens tonight. Telephone.

458
00:29:06,079 --> 00:29:09,541
I don't want to be the messenger
who has to tell Schumacher about this.

459
00:29:09,625 --> 00:29:13,378
He doesn't work at this network anymore.
Mr. Ruddy fired him last night.

460
00:29:13,462 --> 00:29:16,423
Bob McDonough is running
the News Division now.

461
00:29:17,841 --> 00:29:19,843
Bob McDonough in News, please.

462
00:29:21,345 --> 00:29:23,472
I don't know.

463
00:29:23,555 --> 00:29:26,016
I may teach or write a book...

464
00:29:26,099 --> 00:29:30,187
whatever the hell one does when one
approaches the autumn of one's years.

465
00:29:32,981 --> 00:29:34,900
My God! Is that me?

466
00:29:35,692 --> 00:29:38,195
Was I ever that young?

467
00:29:38,278 --> 00:29:40,697
No, Howard brought in a picture
of Ed Murrow...

468
00:29:40,781 --> 00:29:43,242
and the CBS gang
when we were there.

469
00:29:43,325 --> 00:29:44,868
You wouldn't believe it!

470
00:29:44,952 --> 00:29:47,079
Walter Cronkite, Harry Reasoner...

471
00:29:47,120 --> 00:29:49,164
Hollenbeck, Bob Trout.

472
00:29:49,248 --> 00:29:51,166
Is that you?

473
00:29:52,334 --> 00:29:56,088
Yeah. Okay, Dick,
we'll be in touch.

474
00:29:56,171 --> 00:30:00,592
Remember this kid you sent to interview
Cleveland Amory on vivisection?

475
00:30:04,304 --> 00:30:06,557
What's so funny?

476
00:30:09,142 --> 00:30:12,688
I jump out of bed in my pajamas,
I grab my raincoat, I run downstairs.

477
00:30:12,771 --> 00:30:15,399
I run out to the street
and hail a cab.

478
00:30:15,482 --> 00:30:20,487
I yell at the driver, "Take me to the
middle of the George Washington Bridge."

479
00:30:22,614 --> 00:30:26,285
And the driver says,
"Don't do it, buddy. Don't do it!

480
00:30:26,368 --> 00:30:28,871
You're young. You've got
your whole life ahead of you."

481
00:30:29,830 --> 00:30:32,166
Wait a minute.

482
00:30:32,249 --> 00:30:36,753
If you think that's funny,
wait till you hear this.

483
00:30:36,837 --> 00:30:38,797
I've come from Hackett's office.

484
00:30:38,839 --> 00:30:41,633
He wants to put Howard
back on the air tonight.

485
00:30:41,675 --> 00:30:44,761
Apparently the ratings went up
five points last night...

486
00:30:44,845 --> 00:30:48,140
and he wants Howard to go back on
and do his "angry man" thing.

487
00:30:48,182 --> 00:30:50,309
What are you talking about?

488
00:30:50,350 --> 00:30:53,437
They want Howard to go back on
and yell "bullshit."

489
00:30:56,023 --> 00:30:57,983
They want Howard to go on...

490
00:30:58,025 --> 00:31:00,027
spontaneously letting out
his anger.

491
00:31:00,110 --> 00:31:03,071
A latter-day prophet
denouncing the hypocrisies of our times.

492
00:31:03,155 --> 00:31:05,365
That sounds pretty good!

493
00:31:06,283 --> 00:31:07,701
Who's "they"?

494
00:31:07,784 --> 00:31:10,454
Hackett. Chaney was there.

495
00:31:10,537 --> 00:31:13,665
The Legal Affairs guy.
Oh, and that girl from programming.

496
00:31:13,707 --> 00:31:16,168
Christensen?
What's she got to do with this?

497
00:31:16,210 --> 00:31:19,004
- Are you kidding?
- I'm not kidding.

498
00:31:19,046 --> 00:31:22,799
I said, "We're running
a news department here, not a circus.

499
00:31:22,883 --> 00:31:25,427
And Howard Beale's
not a bearded lady.

500
00:31:25,511 --> 00:31:28,138
If you think I'll go along with
this bastardization of the news...

501
00:31:28,222 --> 00:31:31,642
you can have my resignation
along with Max Schumacher's.

502
00:31:31,725 --> 00:31:37,523
- I'm speaking for Howard Beale and..."
- That's my job you're turning down.

503
00:31:37,606 --> 00:31:40,442
I'd go nuts
without some kind of work.

504
00:31:40,526 --> 00:31:44,530
What's wrong with being an angry prophet
denouncing the hypocrisies of our times?

505
00:31:44,613 --> 00:31:46,323
What do you think, Max?

506
00:31:46,406 --> 00:31:50,619
Do you want to be an angry prophet
denouncing the hypocrisies of our times?

507
00:31:50,702 --> 00:31:55,165
Yeah, I'd like to be an angry prophet
denouncing the hypocrisies of our times.

508
00:31:56,458 --> 00:31:58,460
Then grab it!

509
00:32:04,925 --> 00:32:06,885
- Afternoon, Mr. Ruddy.
- Afternoon.

510
00:32:06,927 --> 00:32:08,887
Good afternoon, Mr. Ruddy.

511
00:32:12,015 --> 00:32:14,351
- He's waiting for you.
- Thank you.

512
00:32:20,649 --> 00:32:24,027
Nelson Chaney tells me Beale
may actually go on the air this evening.

513
00:32:25,821 --> 00:32:28,157
As far as I know,
Howard's going to do it.

514
00:32:30,784 --> 00:32:33,495
- Are you gonna sit still for this?
- Yes.

515
00:32:33,579 --> 00:32:36,290
I think Hackett's overstepped himself.

516
00:32:36,373 --> 00:32:38,917
There's some kind of
corporate maneuvering going on.

517
00:32:39,001 --> 00:32:41,545
Hackett is clearly forcing
a confrontation.

518
00:32:41,628 --> 00:32:43,797
That would account for his behavior
at the stockholders' meeting.

519
00:32:43,881 --> 00:32:48,468
However, I think he's making a serious
mistake with this Beale business.

520
00:32:48,552 --> 00:32:51,680
I suspect CCA will be upset...

521
00:32:51,763 --> 00:32:53,724
at Hackett's presumptuousness.

522
00:32:53,807 --> 00:32:55,934
Certainly Mr. Jensen will.

523
00:32:56,018 --> 00:32:59,563
So I'm going to let Hackett
have his head for a while.

524
00:32:59,646 --> 00:33:02,316
He just might lose it
over this Beale business.

525
00:33:06,528 --> 00:33:09,323
I'd like you to reconsider
your resignation.

526
00:33:09,406 --> 00:33:11,909
I assume Hackett
wouldn't take such steps...

527
00:33:11,992 --> 00:33:14,286
without some support
on the CCA board.

528
00:33:14,328 --> 00:33:17,206
I'll have to go directly to Mr. Jensen.

529
00:33:17,289 --> 00:33:20,501
When that happens, I'm going to need
every friend I've got...

530
00:33:20,584 --> 00:33:24,296
and I don't want Hackett's people
in all the divisional positions.

531
00:33:24,338 --> 00:33:26,548
So I'd like you to stay on.

532
00:33:31,094 --> 00:33:32,513
Of course.

533
00:33:34,223 --> 00:33:36,975
Thank you, Max.

534
00:33:37,017 --> 00:33:39,478
This has been
the "UBS Evening News"...

535
00:33:39,561 --> 00:33:41,980
with Howard Beale.

536
00:33:42,064 --> 00:33:44,691
The initial response to the new
"Howard Beale Show"...

537
00:33:44,775 --> 00:33:46,818
was not auspicatory.

538
00:33:46,902 --> 00:33:48,946
The press was,
without exception, hostile...

539
00:33:49,029 --> 00:33:51,198
and industry reaction negative.

540
00:33:51,281 --> 00:33:53,617
The ratings for the Thursday
and Friday shows...

541
00:33:53,700 --> 00:33:56,203
were both 14,
but Monday's rating dropped a point...

542
00:33:56,286 --> 00:33:59,540
clearly suggesting the novelty
was wearing off.

543
00:34:01,375 --> 00:34:03,544
Did you know there are
a number of psychics...

544
00:34:03,627 --> 00:34:06,547
working as licensed brokers
on Wall Street?

545
00:34:06,630 --> 00:34:09,049
Some counsel their clients
by use of tarot cards.

546
00:34:09,132 --> 00:34:12,845
They're all pretty successful,
even in a bear market and selling short.

547
00:34:12,928 --> 00:34:16,515
I met one of them last week
and thought of doing a show around her.

548
00:34:16,598 --> 00:34:19,226
"The Wayward Witch of Wall Street."
Something like that.

549
00:34:19,309 --> 00:34:21,812
But if her tips were any good,
she could wreck the market.

550
00:34:21,895 --> 00:34:27,442
I called her this morning and asked her
how she was on predicting the future.

551
00:34:27,526 --> 00:34:30,195
She said she was
occasionally prescient.

552
00:34:30,279 --> 00:34:34,908
"For example," she said,
"I just had a vision of you...

553
00:34:34,992 --> 00:34:37,995
sitting in an office
with a craggy, middle-aged man...

554
00:34:38,078 --> 00:34:41,498
with whom you are
or will be emotionally involved."

555
00:34:41,582 --> 00:34:43,167
And here I am.

556
00:34:45,627 --> 00:34:48,172
She does all this with tarot cards?

557
00:34:48,255 --> 00:34:51,133
This one operates
on parapsychology.

558
00:34:51,216 --> 00:34:55,512
She has trance-like episodes
and feels things in her energy field.

559
00:34:56,471 --> 00:35:00,184
- This lady could be very useful to you.
- In what way?

560
00:35:00,225 --> 00:35:02,853
You put on a news show.

561
00:35:02,936 --> 00:35:06,148
And here's somebody who can predict
tomorrow's news for you.

562
00:35:06,231 --> 00:35:08,567
Her name, aptly enough, is Sibyl.

563
00:35:08,609 --> 00:35:10,569
Sibyl the Soothsayer.

564
00:35:10,611 --> 00:35:13,197
You could give her
two minutes of trance...

565
00:35:13,280 --> 00:35:15,908
at the end of the "Howard Beale Show,"
say once a week, Friday...

566
00:35:15,949 --> 00:35:18,410
which is suggestively occult,
and she could oraculate.

567
00:35:19,620 --> 00:35:22,581
Then next week everyone tunes in to see
how good her predictions were.

568
00:35:23,707 --> 00:35:25,709
Maybe she could do the weather.

569
00:35:28,045 --> 00:35:31,006
Your "Network News Show" will need help
if it's going to hold.

570
00:35:31,089 --> 00:35:33,550
Beale doesn't do the "angry man" thing
well at all.

571
00:35:33,634 --> 00:35:35,677
He's too kvetchy.
He's being irascible.

572
00:35:35,761 --> 00:35:38,931
We want a prophet, not a curmudgeon.
He should do more apocalyptic doom.

573
00:35:38,972 --> 00:35:42,809
I think you should have some writers
write some jeremiads for him.

574
00:35:44,186 --> 00:35:46,438
I see you don't fancy my suggestions.

575
00:35:48,649 --> 00:35:50,484
You're not serious?

576
00:35:50,567 --> 00:35:52,277
I'm serious.

577
00:35:53,821 --> 00:35:56,323
The fact is, I could make
your Beale show...

578
00:35:56,406 --> 00:36:00,369
the highest-rated news show in TV
if you'd let me have a crack at it.

579
00:36:01,328 --> 00:36:03,580
What do you mean,
"have a crack at it"?

580
00:36:03,664 --> 00:36:05,499
I'd like to program it for you.

581
00:36:05,582 --> 00:36:07,167
Develop it.

582
00:36:07,251 --> 00:36:11,964
I wouldn't interfere with
the news itself, but TV is show biz...

583
00:36:12,005 --> 00:36:15,968
and even the news has to have
a little showmanship.

584
00:36:16,009 --> 00:36:18,303
My God, you are serious.

585
00:36:18,345 --> 00:36:22,516
I watched your six o'clock news today.
It's straight tabloid.

586
00:36:22,599 --> 00:36:26,103
You had a minute and a half of that lady
riding naked in Central Park...

587
00:36:26,186 --> 00:36:29,273
but you had less than a minute
of hard national and international news.

588
00:36:29,356 --> 00:36:32,067
It was all sex, scandal,
brutal crime, sports...

589
00:36:32,150 --> 00:36:35,487
children with incurable diseases
and lost puppies.

590
00:36:35,529 --> 00:36:38,949
So I won't listen to protestations
of high standards of journalism...

591
00:36:39,032 --> 00:36:41,869
when you're on the streets, soliciting
audiences like the rest of us.

592
00:36:41,952 --> 00:36:45,956
All I'm saying is, if you're going
to hustle, at least do it right.

593
00:36:46,039 --> 00:36:49,126
I'm going to bring this up at tomorrow's
meeting, but I don't like hassles.

594
00:36:49,209 --> 00:36:52,588
I was hoping we could work this out
between us. That's why I'm here.

595
00:36:54,131 --> 00:36:57,509
And I was hoping you were looking for
an emotional involvement...

596
00:36:57,551 --> 00:36:59,761
with a craggy, middle-aged man.

597
00:37:01,305 --> 00:37:03,307
I wouldn't rule that out entirely.

598
00:37:06,727 --> 00:37:09,062
All right, Diana...

599
00:37:09,146 --> 00:37:12,858
bring up all your ideas at the meeting,
because if you don't, I will.

600
00:37:14,359 --> 00:37:16,862
I think Howard's making
a goddamn fool of himself...

601
00:37:16,904 --> 00:37:21,033
and so does everybody that Howard
and I know in this industry.

602
00:37:21,116 --> 00:37:23,494
It was a fluke.
Didn't work.

603
00:37:24,745 --> 00:37:27,831
So tomorrow, Howard goes back
to the old format...

604
00:37:27,915 --> 00:37:31,793
and all of this gutter depravity
comes to an end.

605
00:37:43,472 --> 00:37:45,349
I don't get it.

606
00:37:46,808 --> 00:37:49,811
You hung around until 7:30
and then came down here...

607
00:37:49,895 --> 00:37:52,814
just to pitch a couple
of loony show-biz ideas...

608
00:37:52,898 --> 00:37:56,777
when you knew goddamn well
I'd laugh you right out of the office.

609
00:37:56,860 --> 00:37:59,238
I don't get it.

610
00:37:59,321 --> 00:38:02,157
What's your scam in this?

611
00:38:02,241 --> 00:38:07,621
My visit here tonight was a gesture made
out of your stature in the industry...

612
00:38:08,956 --> 00:38:11,625
and because I personally admired you
since I was a kid...

613
00:38:11,708 --> 00:38:14,211
majoring in speech
at the University of Missouri.

614
00:38:15,504 --> 00:38:19,258
Sooner or later, with or without you,
I'm going to take over your news show.

615
00:38:19,341 --> 00:38:21,885
I figured I might as well start tonight.

616
00:38:23,136 --> 00:38:25,848
I think I once gave a lecture...

617
00:38:25,931 --> 00:38:29,184
at the University of Missouri.

618
00:38:29,268 --> 00:38:33,939
I was in the audience. I had
a schoolgirl crush on you for months.

619
00:38:35,566 --> 00:38:38,944
If we could get back for a moment
to that gypsy who predicted...

620
00:38:38,986 --> 00:38:43,240
all that about emotional involvements
and middle-aged men...

621
00:38:44,449 --> 00:38:46,869
what are you doing
for dinner tonight?

622
00:38:56,170 --> 00:38:58,881
I can't make it tonight.
Call me tomorrow.

623
00:39:01,383 --> 00:39:04,553
- Do you have a favorite restaurant?
- I eat anything.

624
00:39:05,929 --> 00:39:08,140
I get a feeling I'm being made.

625
00:39:08,182 --> 00:39:09,641
You are.

626
00:39:10,809 --> 00:39:13,979
I've got to warn you.
I don't do anything on my first date.

627
00:39:14,021 --> 00:39:15,480
We'll see.

628
00:39:21,487 --> 00:39:23,739
Schmuck, what are you getting into?

629
00:39:45,219 --> 00:39:49,264
I was married for four years
and pretended to be happy.

630
00:39:49,348 --> 00:39:51,975
I had six years of analysis
and pretended to be sane.

631
00:39:53,769 --> 00:39:56,438
My husband ran off
with his boyfriend...

632
00:39:56,522 --> 00:40:01,109
and I had an affair with my analyst who
told me I was the worst lay he ever had.

633
00:40:02,402 --> 00:40:05,280
I can't tell you how many men
have told me what a lousy lay I am.

634
00:40:06,156 --> 00:40:08,575
I apparently have
a masculine temperament.

635
00:40:08,659 --> 00:40:12,538
I arouse quickly,
consummate prematurely...

636
00:40:12,579 --> 00:40:15,666
and I can't wait to get my clothes
back on and get out of that bedroom.

637
00:40:16,875 --> 00:40:20,838
I seem to be inept at everything
except my work.

638
00:40:21,713 --> 00:40:23,966
I'm good at my work.

639
00:40:24,049 --> 00:40:26,593
So I confine myself to that.

640
00:40:26,677 --> 00:40:30,138
All I want out of life
is a 30 share and a 20 rating.

641
00:40:31,723 --> 00:40:33,851
You're married, surely?

642
00:40:35,435 --> 00:40:36,854
Twenty-five years.

643
00:40:37,896 --> 00:40:41,191
I have a married daughter in Seattle
who's six months pregnant...

644
00:40:41,275 --> 00:40:46,405
and a younger girl who's starting
at Northwestern in January.

645
00:40:49,283 --> 00:40:51,201
Well, Max, here we are.

646
00:40:53,287 --> 00:40:56,039
Middle-aged man reaffirming
his middle-aged manhood...

647
00:40:56,123 --> 00:40:59,084
and a terrified young woman
with a father complex.

648
00:40:59,168 --> 00:41:01,670
What sort of script
can we make out of this?

649
00:41:03,755 --> 00:41:08,135
Corridor gossip says that you're
Frank Hackett's backstage girl.

650
00:41:09,178 --> 00:41:10,596
I'm not.

651
00:41:12,306 --> 00:41:15,642
Frank's a corporation man,
body and soul.

652
00:41:15,726 --> 00:41:17,728
He has no loves, lusts
or allegiances...

653
00:41:17,769 --> 00:41:21,231
that are not consummately directed
toward becoming a CCA board member.

654
00:41:21,315 --> 00:41:24,151
Why should he bother with me?
I'm not even a stockholder.

655
00:41:26,028 --> 00:41:30,282
What about your loves,
lusts and allegiances?

656
00:41:30,365 --> 00:41:32,534
Is your wife in town?

657
00:41:32,618 --> 00:41:34,036
Yes.

658
00:41:35,329 --> 00:41:37,789
Then we better go to my place.

659
00:41:39,166 --> 00:41:42,127
I can't hear you.
You'll have to talk a little louder.

660
00:41:48,842 --> 00:41:51,887
Yes, I hear you.

661
00:41:55,474 --> 00:41:56,892
Yes.

662
00:41:59,686 --> 00:42:01,146
Yes.

663
00:42:07,069 --> 00:42:08,529
Why me?

664
00:42:10,489 --> 00:42:12,699
I said, "Why me?"

665
00:42:33,053 --> 00:42:35,013
Howard in his office?

666
00:42:36,181 --> 00:42:41,228
I'm killing this whole screwball
"angry prophet" thing.

667
00:42:41,311 --> 00:42:43,522
Tonight we go back to straight news.

668
00:42:50,404 --> 00:42:53,991
Yeah? Max, I'm telling you he's fine.

669
00:42:54,032 --> 00:42:57,119
He's been sharp all day.
He's been as funny as hell.

670
00:42:57,202 --> 00:42:59,413
Had everybody cracking up
at the rundown meeting.

671
00:42:59,496 --> 00:43:01,498
I told him!

672
00:43:02,291 --> 00:43:03,709
Cue VTA.

673
00:43:04,501 --> 00:43:05,919
Ready two.

674
00:43:08,213 --> 00:43:11,508
- Cue announcer.
- The "UBS Evening News"...

675
00:43:11,592 --> 00:43:13,594
with Howard Beale.

676
00:43:14,595 --> 00:43:18,432
Last night I was awakened
from a fitful sleep...

677
00:43:18,515 --> 00:43:21,185
shortly after 2:00 in the morning...

678
00:43:21,226 --> 00:43:24,313
by a shrill, sibilant,
faceless voice.

679
00:43:24,396 --> 00:43:28,025
I couldn't make it out at first
in the dark bedroom.

680
00:43:29,568 --> 00:43:32,196
I said, "I'm sorry.
You'll have to talk a little louder."

681
00:43:32,237 --> 00:43:35,949
- What do you want me to do?
- Nothing.

682
00:43:36,033 --> 00:43:39,328
The voice said to me,
"I want you to tell the truth.

683
00:43:39,411 --> 00:43:42,247
Not easy to do, because the people
don't want to know the truth."

684
00:43:42,331 --> 00:43:45,083
I said, "You're kidding?

685
00:43:45,125 --> 00:43:47,085
What should I know about the truth?"

686
00:43:47,127 --> 00:43:51,715
But the voice said to me,
"Don't worry about the truth."

687
00:43:51,757 --> 00:43:53,759
I will put the words in your mouth."

688
00:43:54,801 --> 00:43:56,762
I said,
"Is this the burning bush?

689
00:43:56,803 --> 00:43:58,263
I'm not Moses."

690
00:43:58,305 --> 00:44:01,600
The voice said, "I'm not God.
What has that got to do with it?"

691
00:44:01,642 --> 00:44:06,021
The voice said, "We're not talking
about eternal, absolute truth.

692
00:44:06,104 --> 00:44:08,816
We're talking about impermanent,
transient, human truth!

693
00:44:08,899 --> 00:44:11,777
I don't expect people
to be capable of truth...

694
00:44:11,860 --> 00:44:14,404
but at least you're capable
of self-preservation."

695
00:44:15,489 --> 00:44:19,243
I said, "Why me?"

696
00:44:19,284 --> 00:44:22,037
The voice said, "Because you're
on television, dummy."

697
00:44:22,120 --> 00:44:24,331
Beautiful.

698
00:44:24,414 --> 00:44:27,543
"Forty million Americans listen to you,
and after the show, maybe 50 million.

699
00:44:27,626 --> 00:44:31,839
I'm not asking you to walk the land
in sackcloth preaching the Armageddon.

700
00:44:31,922 --> 00:44:33,340
You're on TV."

